26. Friyida curarum fomenta] It is not easy to decide upon the meaning of ‘ fomenta' here. Some suppose it signifies those selfish objects, such as honour, riches, &c., which seem to foster (‘ fovere ') care, and which make the heart cold and the feelings dull. Others apply it to similar objects 3 but as the remedies by which care is sought to be aueviated are “ fomenta vulnus nil malum levantia '’ (Epod. xi. 17), 1 incline to the latter myself. (See note on the above Epode). They are still ‘ frigidass in the sense above given.
